MYSQL-TEST-RUN SCRIPTS
----------------------

This directory contains the modified test and result scripts for mysql-test-run.

INSTALLATION
------------

To install the tests:

1. Make a backup copy of your current <mysql-install-dir>/mysql-test directory, where <mysql-install-dir> is the path to the MySQL installation directory or source tree.


2. Remove the directories 'extra', 'include', 'r', 't' and 'suite', and create symbolic links to all the directories in the 'mysql-test' directory here.

4. Edit the file <mysql-install-dir>/share/mysql/mysql_system_tables_data.sql, and add the following lines to the end of the file:

-- Entry for loading PBXT plugin
INSERT plugin VALUES('PBXT', 'libpbxt.so');

5. Compile and install the PBXT plug-in in the <mysql-install-dir>/lib/mysql directory, for example:

./configure --with-mysql=<mysql-source-tree> --libdir=<mysql-install-dir>/lib/mysql

6. Start mysql test run:

$ cd <mysql-source>/mysql-test
$ ./mysql-test-run --mysqld=--default-storage-engine=pbxt

